📘 FULL STACK DEVELOPMENT – CA II
Employee Management System (Backend using Express.js & MongoDB)

1️⃣ INTRODUCTION
The Employee Management System is a backend-based application developed using Node.js, Express.js, and MongoDB.
The project follows the RESTful API architecture and provides endpoints to perform CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) on multiple resources such as Employees, Departments, Designations, Attendance, and Leaves.
The APIs are tested using Postman, and the data is stored and verified using MongoDB Compass.
This system helps in managing employee-related data efficiently and demonstrates real-world backend development concepts.

2️⃣ OBJECTIVES OF THE PROJECT
The main objectives of this project are:
To design and implement RESTful APIs using Express.js
To perform CRUD operations on multiple resources
To store and manage data using MongoDB
To establish relationships between collections using ObjectId
To test APIs using Postman
To return appropriate HTTP status codes for each operation

