5️⃣ DATABASE DESIGN
The database used for this project is EmployeeDB.
The following collections are created to manage different resources:
Employees
Departments
Designations
Attendance
Leaves
Each collection stores structured data, and relationships are maintained using ObjectId references.

6️⃣ COLLECTION DETAILS
Employees Collection
name
email
dob
designation
joiningDate
salary
status
departmentId (Reference)
createdAt, updatedAt
Purpose: Stores complete employee details.

Departments Collection
name
code
createdAt, updatedAt
Purpose: Stores department information.

Designations Collection
title
level
departmentId
Purpose: Stores designation details linked with departments.

Attendance Collection
employeeId
loginTime
logoutTime
date
Purpose: Stores login and logout details of employees.

Leaves Collection
employeeId
leaveType
startDate
endDate
status
Purpose: Stores employee leave records.

7️⃣ API ENDPOINTS
Employee APIs
HTTP Method
Endpoint
Description
POST
/api/employees
Add new employee
GET
/api/employees
Get all employees
GET
/api/employees/:id
